Class Environment

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.xebialabs.deployit.plugin.api.udm.base.BaseConfigurationItem
      • com.xebialabs.deployit.plugin.api.udm.Environment
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ConfigurationItem, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<BaseConfigurationItem>
    @Metadata(description="Groups infrastructure CIs and dictionaries and serves as a target for deployment.",
          root=ENVIRONMENTS)
@TypeIcon("icons/types/udm.Environment.svg")
public class Environment
extends BaseConfigurationItem
    An Environment is a grouping of Container CIs (such as hosts, servers, clusters, etc.) and Dictionary items.

    An Environment is used as the target of a deployment, allowing Deployables to be mapped to members of the environment.
